Advice On Filing For Unemployment Benefits: Document Everything And Be PersistentEnlarge this image toggle caption Andrew Kelly/Reuters Andrew Kelly/ReutersUpdated on April 6 at 9:37 1.m.
ETA record 10 million people filed for initial unemployment benefits in the past two weeks, with many more anticipated in coming weeks.
A $2 trillion relief bill was signed by President Trump, with a $250 billion expansion of unemployment benefits.
States are also trying to staff up their unemployment offices.
If you're eligible, check your state's unemployment insurance program, which has updated information relating to filing during this coronavirus period.